R_Workshop_WHRI

Author: Jonathan Simkin Date: May 19th 2020

A short and sweet R basics tutorial for a (bright and enthusiasti) cohort of MPH Students.

Find the R markdown here. Covers a short exploratory analysis of Gapminder dataset.

Awesome packages used here:

  • Tidyverse
  • plotly
  • ggthemes
  • hrbrthemes
  • kableExtra
  • viridisLite

DT did not make it into the rmd but I highly recommend this package for creating data tables.

Have fun with R!
